# iter-113 Theme C: pin line endings so Windows checkouts stop producing CRLF
# sources. Git for Windows defaults to core.autocrlf=true, which rewrites LF ->
# CRLF on checkout; that broke `include_str!`-based source-pin tests (e.g.
# `unit_error_enums_non_exhaustive`) whose `\n` patterns never matched the CRLF
# working tree. `text=auto eol=lf` normalizes every text file to LF in the repo
# AND in the working tree on all platforms, making those tests platform-stable.
# The iter-112 CRLF normalization inside that test is kept as belt-and-braces.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary fixtures must never be line-ending munged.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
